                    <heading>Defence</heading>
                    <p id="CZ.DIR.712">
          As assessed at November 2023, the total active armed forces numbered 26,600, including an army of 14,700 and an air force of 5,850. The Czech Republic joined 
          <xr pageref="N" ref="NATO.IO">the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO)</xr>
           in March 1999. Following the full-scale invasion of Ukraine by the Russian Federation in February 2022, the Czech Republic increased spending on defence and donated military equipment to Ukraine. A Defence Cooperation Agreement with the USA was agreed in April. The Czech Republic published its new security strategy during 2023.
        </p>
